ZH: 不要隨便摸人家的東西。
EN: Don't touch other people's things without permission.

ZH: 小孩子喜歡摸各種東西。
EN: Children like to touch everything.

ZH: 這個杯子摸起來很光滑。
EN: This cup feels very smooth to the touch.

ZH: 表示愛意可以摸對方的手。
EN: Showing affection can involve touching hands.

ZH: 請不要摸那個藥品。
EN: Please do not touch that medication.

ZH: 醫生要摸病人的脈搏。
EN: Doctors need to feel the patient's pulse.

ZH: 女生總是摸自己的頭髮。
EN: Girls always touch their own hair.

ZH: 摸到狗的頭會使人感到安慰。
EN: Patting a dog's head can be comforting.

ZH: 孩子們喜歡在沙灘上摸沙子。
EN: Children enjoy touching the sand at the beach.

ZH: 這件衣服的質地很好，摸起來很舒服。
EN: The fabric of this clothing is very good, feels comfortable to touch.

ZH: 長時間使用手機可能會引起手指酸痛，因為常常需要摸觸屏幕。
EN: Long-term use of mobile phones may cause finger pain, as there is frequent need to touch the screen.

ZH: 他喜歡摸著鋼琴上的琴鍵彈奏音樂。
EN: He enjoys touching the piano keys and playing music.

ZH: 請不要一直摸我的肩膀。
EN: Please stop touching my shoulder constantly.

ZH: 在暗處識別物件時通常通過摸的方式進行。
EN: When recognizing objects in the dark, it is usually done through touch.

ZH: 這隻貓咪很親人，喜歡被摸摸。
EN: This cat is friendly and likes to be petted.

ZH: 孩子在成長過程中，需要大量接觸和摸索不同的事物以發展感官。
EN: Children need a lot of contact and exploration of different things through touch to develop their senses.

ZH: 摸摸狗狗的耳朵會讓它感到開心。
EN: Petting a dog's ears can make it happy.

ZH: 這塊布料摸起來很粗糙。
EN: This piece of fabric feels rough to the touch.

ZH: 我常常在寫作時需要摸索創意。
EN: I often need to feel my way through creativity when writing.

ZH: 老師在教室裡講解數學問題，同時在黑板上摸索著指導學生。
EN: The teacher explains math problems in the classroom, while guiding students on the blackboard through touch.
